500|$|A point {{process is}} a {{collection}} of points randomly located on some mathematical space such as the real line, -dimensional Euclidean space, or more abstract spaces. Sometimes the term point process is not preferred, as historically the word process denoted an evolution of some system in [...] time, so a point {{process is a}}lso called a random point field. There are different interpretations of a point process, such a random counting measure or a random set. Some authors regard a point process and stochastic process as two different objects such that a point process is a random object that arises from or is associated with a stochastic process, though it has been remarked that the difference between <b>point</b> <b>processes</b> and stochastic processes is not clear.|$|E
